        <prompt>What role did the Union League play in organizing African American voters?</prompt>
        <options>
            <option letter="a">Provided political education and protection for black voters</option>
            <option letter="b">Opposed black voting rights</option>
            <option letter="c">Supported Confederate interests</option>
            <option letter="d">Focused on economic development</option>
        </options>
        <answer>a</answer>
        <explanation>The Union League provided political education to newly enfranchised African Americans and offered protection when they exercised their voting rights.</explanation>
