    <question>
        <prompt>What was the significance of the Civil Rights Act of 1875?</prompt>
        <options>
            <option letter="a">Last major civil rights legislation until the 1950s</option>
            <option letter="b">First voting rights law</option>
            <option letter="c">Created the Freedmen's Bureau</option>
            <option letter="d">Established military districts</option>
        </options>
        <answer>a</answer>
        <explanation>The Civil Rights Act of 1875 was the last major civil rights legislation passed by Congress until the Civil Rights Movement of the 1950s and 1960s.</explanation>
    </question>
    <question>
        <prompt>What was the purpose of the "pig law" in South Carolina?</prompt>
        <options>
            <option letter="a">To imprison African Americans through harsh theft penalties</option>
            <option letter="b">To regulate livestock farming</option>
            <option letter="c">To improve food safety</option>
            <option letter="d">To support agricultural development</option>
        </options>
        <answer>a</answer>
        <explanation>The "pig law" made theft of farm animals a major felony, used to imprison African Americans through disproportionate enforcement and harsh penalties.</explanation>
    </question>
